A '''towelket''' (タオルケット taoruketto) is a type of [[Bedding|bed linen]] resembling a large beach towel and used in [[Japan]] to cover oneself in hot weather. 

The word is a [[portmanteau]] of the English word "towel"（タオル） and ''ketto'', which is a clipped form of the English word "blanket."（ブランケット）

